The paper proposes a novel approach for quantifying consensus in rankings, which is a common problem in group decision making and information systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). These sub-categories are all relevant to the problem of ranking and consensus, and are likely to contain similar research on the topic.
